1965;;The Alphabet Murders;;British;;Frank Tashlin;;Tony Randall, Anita Ekberg, Robert Morley;;mystery;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Alphabet_Murders;;Albert Aachen, a clown with a unique diving act, is found dead, the murder weapon happens to be a poison dart. When a woman named Betty Barnard becomes the next victim, detective Hercule Poirot suspects that Sir Carmichael Clarke could be in grave danger.As he and Captain Hastings look into the crimes, a beautiful woman with an interesting monogram named Amanda Beatrice Cross becomes the focus of their investigation, at least until she leaps into the Thames.